           SHORT="a simple and friendly environment for sending and receiving mail"
cat << EOF
S-nail provides a simple and friendly environment for sending and receiving
mail. It is intended to provide the functionality of the POSIX mailx(1)
command, but is MIME capable and optionally offers extensions for line
editing, S/MIME, SMTP and POP3, among others. It divides incoming mail into
its constituent messages and allows the user to deal with them in any order.
S-mailx heraldic animal It offers many COMMANDS and INTERNAL VARIABLES for
manipulating messages and sending mail. It offers the user simple editing
capabilities to ease the composition of outgoing messages, as well as providing
the ability to define and send to names which address groups of users,
and increasingly powerful and reliable non-interactive scripting capabilities.
EOF
